connect

public static AmazonEC2PortType connect(File privateKey,
                                        File x509certificate)
                                 throws IOException,
                                        GeneralSecurityException
Creates a JAX-WS proxy object that you can use to talk to EC2.

Parameters:
privateKey - Private key that proves your identity to EC2. This is the "pk-*.pem" file.
x509certificate - X509 certificate, which is the public key. This is the "cert-*.pem" file.
Returns:
A proxy object that exposes EC2 SOAP API as method calls. This object is multi-thread safe.
Throws:
IOException - If key files fail to load.
GeneralSecurityException - If cryptography related problem is encounted while handling the key.
WebServiceException - If Metro fails.
